<br><center><img src="http://www.everworld.net/images/datel.gif" width=46 height=22 border=0><img src="http://www.everworld.net/images/dateblnk.gif" width=100 height=22 border=0><img src="http://www.everworld.net/images/dater.gif" width=306 height=22 border=0></center><BR><P ALIGN=CENTER><b>In Reply To:</b> <A HREF="http://www.everworld.net/cgi-local/forum/erollisi_marr.cgi?read=37" TARGET=_self>dont want to be a player killer PVP</A> (fiberino)
</STRONG><FONT SIZE=2 color=#F4D99F FACE=arial>
<P>> how do i get back to normal a non pvp i gave

<BR>&gt; a book to the priest of discord and i did
<BR>&gt; not know and DO NOT want to start over.
<BR>&gt; please help me.
<P>I am also a PvP character, but by choice. I actually enjoy being a PvP character as it forces a bit of independance that many shirk. My character is a 10th level Wizard named Dakinis in Faydwer.
<P>I hear that there is a PvP guild on Antonica. I would suggest that you seek it out as you will find many allies there. Despite popular belief, most PvP characters are quite friendly and generous to other PvPers. A virtual world example of how a people persecuted stick together.
<P>Cheers
</FONT></td></tr></table></P>
